Password Manager SPA

A secure, single-page application for managing your passwords with built-in password generation capabilities.

Features

- User authentication (login/signup)
- Secure password storage with encryption
- Password strength evaluation
- Password generator with customizable options
- Search functionality for stored passwords
- Responsive design


Usage Guide

 1. Account Creation

1. Click on the "Sign Up" tab
2. Enter a username and password
3. Confirm your password
4. The password strength meter will show how strong your password is
5. Click "Sign Up" to create your account

2. Logging In

1. Enter your username and password
2. Click "Login"
3. You'll be taken to the main password manager interface

3. Main Interface Navigation

The app has three main tabs:

Add New Tab
- Add new password entries:
  - Enter the website/application name
  - Enter the username/email
  - Enter the password (or generate one using the Generator tab)
  - Click "Add Password" to save

Saved Tab
- View all your saved passwords in a table
- Search for specific passwords using the search box
- Click the eye icon to reveal/hide a password
- Click the trash icon to delete a password

Generator Tab
- Generate secure passwords with options to:
  - Include uppercase letters (A-Z)
  - Include lowercase letters (a-z)
  - Include numbers (0-9)
  - Include special characters (!@#$%)
  - Adjust password length (4-50 characters)
- Generated passwords include strength evaluation
- Click "Copy" to copy the password to clipboard
- Click "Use This Password" to automatically fill it in the "Add New" form

4. Logging Out

Click the "Logout" button in the top right corner to securely log out of your account.

5. Security Notes

- All passwords are encrypted before being stored
- Your data is saved in your browser's localStorage
- The app includes password strength evaluation to help you create secure passwords
- Always log out when using shared devices

6. Technical details

- Password encryption
- When adding a password, a random salt is generated
- A key is derived from your credentials using PBKDF2
- Your password is encrypted using AES-256 with the derived key
- Only the encrypted version and salt are stored

7. Browser Compatibility

The app should work in all modern browsers including:
- Chrome
- Firefox
- Safari
- Edge
